[
  {
    "file": "benchmark/case-spec.md",
    "line": 75,
    "summary": "§6.1 states \"The workshop/ directory does not exist in the baseline — the Agent must create it,\" but baseline commit 37c159d contains workshop/index.html and 13 hamster photos in workshop/public/hamsters/ — a direct factual contradiction that would confuse any agent about the starting state.",
    "failure_scenario": "An agent reads line 75 and concludes it must create workshop/ from scratch, then finds the directory already exists with assets. It either skips scaffolding steps (missing package.json, vite config) or conflicts with pre-existing content. The \"Agent must create it\" acceptance criterion cannot be meaningfully evaluated because the starting state already satisfies it."
  },
  {
    "file": "benchmark/case-spec.md",
    "line": 47,
    "summary": "MongoDB collection name mismatch: F3 acceptance criteria list \"hamster_memory\" (singular, line 47) but F3 Environment §8.1 lists \"hamster_memories\" (plural, line 195) — agents implementing F3 will not know which name to use.",
    "failure_scenario": "An agent uses 'hamster_memory' for the Mongoose model but queries 'hamster_memories' elsewhere (or vice versa). Mongoose creates two separate collections, queries against the wrong name silently return empty results, and visit/feed tracking data appears to be lost."
  },
  {
    "file": "benchmark/metrics.md",
    "line": 56,
    "summary": "Example references non-existent feature \"F5 阶段 Mongoose schema 缺少 id 字段\" but the benchmark only defines F1, F2, and F3 — a copy-paste artifact from a different project.",
    "failure_scenario": "A data recorder follows the example format verbatim, writing bug reports tagged 'F5' into results.csv. Downstream analysis scripts that filter by feature label (F1/F2/F3) silently drop these mislabeled entries, corrupting the bug count for the benchmark."
  },
  {
    "file": "benchmark/plan.md",
    "line": 36,
    "summary": "Stray triple-backtick fence on line 36 opens a code block that wraps the Chinese-language dependency explanation on line 38 (\"Feature 之间有依赖——F2 依赖 F1…\") in monospace formatting, then closes on line 39 — this critical dependency note is rendered as code and easily skipped by readers.",
    "failure_scenario": "A reader skims the rendered markdown, their eyes skip over the monospace block, and they miss the fact that F2 depends on F1 and F3 depends on F2. They attempt to implement F3 before F2, producing code that won't integrate with the prior feature's API and frontend components."
  },
  {
    "file": "benchmark/metrics.md",
    "line": 47,
    "summary": "Human Intervention Levels table (Level 0–3 with identical definitions) is duplicated verbatim between experiment-protocol.md §5 and metrics.md §4 — if the frozen protocol's definitions are ever updated, metrics.md will silently diverge.",
    "failure_scenario": "A future revision updates the Level definitions in the canonical experiment-protocol.md but misses the copy in metrics.md. Evaluators reference different documents for the same concept and assign different intervention levels to the same event, invalidating cross-workflow comparisons."
  },
  {
    "file": "benchmark/metrics.md",
    "line": 96,
    "summary": "The 30-field CSV header is defined in three places: metrics.md line 96, experiment-protocol.md line 138, and results.csv line 1 — any schema change requires synchronized edits across all three.",
    "failure_scenario": "A new metric column is added to metrics.md but experiment-protocol.md's frozen CSV header is not updated (or vice versa). The results.csv header won't match what the protocol says should be recorded, and data columns get misaligned during aggregation from three workflow branches into the canonical results.csv."
  },
  {
    "file": "benchmark/plan.md",
    "line": 26,
    "summary": "plan.md substantially overlaps with experiment-protocol.md: controlled variables (plan.md §2.1 vs protocol.md §1), feature execution order (§2.2 vs §4), branch strategy (§3 vs §2), and data recording (§4 vs §8) are all restated — plan.md adds almost no unique information beyond its one-paragraph experiment goal (§1).",
    "failure_scenario": "The frozen experiment protocol is updated (e.g., branch naming scheme changes) but plan.md, being a non-authoritative overview, is missed. A reader following plan.md uses the wrong branch prefix or feature order, creating a branch that doesn't match the protocol."
  },
  {
    "file": "benchmark/workflow-notes/superpowers.md",
    "line": 1,
    "summary": "Three completely empty Markdown files (superpowers.md, matt-pocock.md, agent-skills.md) under workflow-notes/ are referenced by README.md line 53 as \"三个 workflow 的深入分析\" (deep analysis of three workflows) but contain zero content and will likely never be filled since they document the workflows being tested rather than test results.",
    "failure_scenario": "A new contributor opens these files expecting workflow documentation to understand the experiment, finds nothing, and wastes time determining whether the files are vestigial or awaiting content. The README directory tree misrepresents what's actually in the repository."
  },
  {
    "file": "benchmark/README.md",
    "line": 40,
    "summary": "Dead placeholder \"实验完成后填写\" (fill in after experiment) in the Observed Results section, plus a reference to a nonexistent \"runs/\" directory on line 55 — both will remain stale if the experiment is never run or if results are recorded only in results.csv.",
    "failure_scenario": "The benchmark documentation is archived without the experiment being run. The 'Observed Results' section remains permanently empty with a dangling placeholder, and the 'runs/' directory link in the navigation tree is a broken reference for anyone browsing the repository."
  },
  {
    "file": "benchmark/experiment-protocol.md",
    "line": 143,
    "summary": "Token recording rules (§8) define elaborate cross-comparison logic for input/output/total tokens, but the protocol itself acknowledges (lines 144-145) that VS Code extension likely does not expose per-session token data — making three CSV columns likely N/A and the comparison rules speculative dead weight in a frozen document.",
    "failure_scenario": "All three workflow runs complete with token columns marked N/A. The complex comparison rules occupy space in the frozen protocol but are never exercised. Meanwhile, no alternative cost metric is proposed, leaving the '成本' (cost) evaluation dimension unmeasured."
  }
]
